            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Worst management. Behaviour towards parents is sometimes pathetic. Too difficult to meet principal. Current receptionist needs to learn how to behave. He without any hesitation addressed me, a parent 'A Stranger'. He must be instructed to behave like that. One of the teacher named Mr.Jimmy Brown, who is the class teacher of my son's class harassed me when I wanted to discuss about the problem my son was facing in class. Mr. Brown directly told he was instructed not to discuss about discipline.This happened on 29th October and immediate mail was sent but till now school doesn't show the minimum courtesy to contact us,the parents of CBS. School sends notice to pay advance fees within 4 days suddenly and without informing parents they told students that they will not be able to seat for final examination. Students ID-card given at the end of the session (5th December).  Corporal punishment is still there. Total mismanagement. Not expected from a reputed missionary school like CBS.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
